Brief scores at tea on the third day of the third Test between South Africa and Australia at Newlands on Saturday. South Africa 311 and 151-3 (A. Markram 84, H. Amla 31; P. Cummins 2-31). Australia 255 (C. Bancroft 77, N. Lyon 47; K. Rabada 4-91, M. Morkel 4-87). Match situation: South Africa lead by 207 runs with seven wickets remaining in the second innings. Toss: South Africa